    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix dead code in HARQ indication packing function\n\n### Summary\nThe `pack_harq_indication_body_value` function in the nfapi P7 packing code contained dead code that read `pdu->instance_length` from input structures and immediately overwrote it with calculated values. This could lead to incorrect message lengths being temporarily used during packing.\n\nThis fix replaces the dead code pattern with a proper placeholder approach that pushes 0 as a placeholder value and then overwrites it with the calculated instance length.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/src/nfapi_p7.c`: Fixed dead code in `pack_harq_indication_body_value` and similar functions by replacing `push16(pdu->instance_length, ...)` with `push16(0, ...)`\n- Also fixed the same pattern in `pack_crc_indication_body_value`, `pack_rach_indication_body_value`, `pack_srs_indication_body_value`, `pack_sr_indication_body_value`, `pack_cqi_indication_body_value`, `pack_nb_harq_indication_body_value`, and `pack_nrach_indication_body_value`\n- Fixed typo \"feild\" to \"field\" in comments\n\n"
}